blurb_text: The 2007 federal election was held on 24 November 2007. In Queensland, the elected candidates were Ian Douglas MacDonald (Liberal), John Joseph Hogg (Australian Labor Party), Sue Boyce (Liberal), Claire Moore (Australian Labor Party), Ron Boswell (The Nationals), and Mark Furner (Australian Labor Party).
